Return Code\: 0 \= Step ran successfully 1 \= Step failed. Inputs\: command - executes ProvisionWeblogicManagedServersV2.py Call Wrapper - Required\: Command that will execute the step as a specific user (by default, sudo su - root/opt/opsware/jython/jython on UNIX targets and jython running as Administrator on Windows targets). Custom KeyStore PassPhrase - Optional\: Password to the custom keystore. Custom KeyStore Path - Optional\: Fully qualified path to the custom keystore file. Custom TrustStore PassPhrase - Optional\: Password to the custom trust store. Custom TrustStore Path - Optional\: Fully qualified path to the custom trust store file. Domain Path - Required\: Fully qualified path that the domain and domain configuration will be created under. For example /opt/weblogic/user_projects/domains. Enable Managed Server SSL - Required\: This parameter will set the managed server to either use or not use the ssl port for communication. Valid options are true or false. Listen Port - Required\: Node Manager listen port Managed Server Admin Ports - Required\: The common secure domain-wide administration port that the admin server and managed server will communicate on. Managed Server Hostnames - Required\: Comma delimited list of hostnames or ip addresses where each managed server will be provisioned. The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally. Managed Server Names - Required\: Comma delimited list of names of Managed Servers to be provisioned. (Example\: Appserver1) The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally. Managed Server Ports - Required\: Comma delimited list of ports that the Managed Servers will listen on. The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally. Managed Server SSL Ports - Optional\: Comma delimited list of SSL ports that the Managed Servers will listen on. The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally. Private Key Alias - Optional\: The keystore attribute that defines the string alias used to store and retrieve the server's private key. Setup Server Custom SSL Stores - Required\: This parameter will set whether you want to run ssl with the demo ssl certificates or with your own custom keystore and trustore. Options are true or false. If true then Custom KeyStore Path, Custom KeyStore PassPhrase, Custom Truststore Path, Custom TrustStore PassPhrase and Private Key Alias have to be set. WLST Call Wrapper - Required\: Fully qualified path to the wlst.sh script. host - Target to run this command against password - Login information for host username - Login information for host protocol - ssh/wmi timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.  Purpose

This workflow will create a Weblogic Manage Server from an existing installation and WebLogic domain.


 Results verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether the creation was successful. Be sure to also perform the following steps\:

   1. View the {DomainPath}/servers/{ManageServerName}/logs/{ManagedServerName}.log file. This file is created when the Managed Server is started up, look for the following\: Server started in RUNNING mode

 Notification plan

Define who should be notified when the workflow succeeds and fails.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Admin Server Hostname - Required\: This is the hostname or ip address that the Admin Server will run on.
    Admin Server Name - Required\: Lable or name given to the Admin Server.
    Admin Server Port - Requried\: This will be the non ssl port that the Admin Server will run on.
    BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory in which to install WebLogic Server. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic.
    Domain Administration Port - Required\: The common secure administration port for this WebLogic Server domain.
    Domain Path - Required\: Fully qualified path that the domain and domain configuration will be created under. For example /opt/weblogic/user_projects/domains.
    Enable Managed Server SSL - Required\:  This parameter will set the managed server to either use or not use the ssl port for communication.  Valid options are true or false.
    Managed Server Admin Ports - Required\: The common secure domain-wide administration port that the admin server and managed server will communicate on.
    Managed Server Hostnames - Required\: Comma delimited list of hostnames or ip addresses where each managed server will be provisioned.  The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally.
    Managed Server Names - Required\: Comma delimited list of names of Managed Servers to be provisioned. (Example\: Appserver1)  The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally.
    Managed Server Ports - Required\: Comma delimited list of ports that the Managed Servers will listen on.  The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally.
    Server.Become User - No description
    Server.Name - No description
    Setup Server Custom SSL Stores - Required\: This parameter will set whether you want to run ssl with the demo ssl certificates or with your own custom keystore and trustore.  Options are true or false.  If true then Custom KeyStore Path, Custom KeyStore PassPhrase, Custom Truststore Path, Custom TrustStore PassPhrase and Private Key Alias have to be set.
    WebLogic User Id - Required\: This will be the WebLogic user that will be used to authenticate with the Admin Server.
    WebLogic User Password - Required\: This will be the password that will be used to authenticate with the Admin Server.
    WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic/wlserver_10.3

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Custom KeyStore Path - Optional\: Fully qualified path to the custom keystore file.
    Managed Server SSL Ports - Optional\: Comma delimited list of SSL ports that the Managed Servers will listen on.  The lists Managed Server Hostnames, Managed Server Names, Managed Server Ports and Managed Server SSL Ports all match up positionally.
    Custom TrustStore Path - Optional\: Fully qualified path to the custom trust store file.
    Custom TrustStore PassPhrase - Optional\: Password to the custom trust store.
    Private Key Alias - Optional\: The keystore attribute that defines the string alias used to store and retrieve the server's private key.
    Custom KeyStore PassPhrase - Optional\: Password to the custom keystore.
    Start Managed Servers - Optional\: Specifies whether or not to start up the managed servers once they have been created.
